com.avaya.csta.async

Interface AsynchronousCallback


  • public interface AsynchronousCallback
    AsynchronousCallback defines methods that are called in response to requests made against the AsynchronousServices.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void handleException(java.lang.Throwable exception)
      Method handleException will be called by AsynchronousServices if the request resulted in an exception being sent back from the server.
      void handleResponse(java.lang.Object response)
      Method handleResponse will be called by AsynchronousServices with the response that was sent back from the server.

    • Method Detail

      • handleResponse

        void handleResponse(java.lang.Object response)
        Method handleResponse will be called by AsynchronousServices with the response that was sent back from the server. The response Object must be cast to the return type expected for the request that was made using AsynchronousServices.
        Parameters:
        response - response from the server.

      • handleException

        void handleException(java.lang.Throwable exception)
        Method handleException will be called by AsynchronousServices if the request resulted in an exception being sent back from the server.
        Parameters:
        exception - Throwable passed back to the server in response to a request.
